'''''Bountiful Harvest''''' is a book by [[University of Houston]] economics professor [[Thomas R. DeGregori]], debunking what he calls "[[antiscience|anti-science]] [[environmental activist]]s", and arguing for the employment modern agricultural innovations such as [[genetically modified organism|bioengineered food]]s, which he claims have increased life expectancy and crop yields, and generally improved human well-being.

The ''[[AgBiotech Reporter]]'' called DeGregori's book "an ideal handbook for anyone who wants to understand the opponents of progress."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cato.org/cgi-bin/Web_store/web_store.cgi?page%3Dbountifulharvest.html%26cart_id%3D |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2002-11-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20021201001315/http://cato.org/cgi-bin/Web_store/web_store.cgi?page=bountifulharvest.html&cart_id= |archivedate=2002-12-01 |df= }}</ref>

