{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}} {{Infobox aircraft occurrence |name = Somali Airlines Flight 40 |occurrence_type = Accident |image = Somali Airlines Fokker F27-600 Friendship Groves.jpg |image_size = 200 |alt = |caption = The accident aircraft before delivery. |date = 20 July 1981 |type = Structural failure due to loss of control in extreme turbulence. |site = [[Bal'ad District|Balad]], Somalia |coordinates = <!--These 17 entries for single-aircraft occurrence:------> |aircraft_type = [[Fokker F27 Friendship|Fokker F27-600 Friendship]] |aircraft_name = |operator = [[Somali Airlines]] |tail_number = 6O-SAY |origin = [[Mogadishu International Airport]], [[Mogadishu]], Somalia |stopover = |stopover0 = |stopover1 = |stopover2 = |stopover3 = |last_stopover = |destination = [[Hargeisa International Airport]], [[Hargeisa]], Somalia |passengers = 44 |crew = 6 |injuries = |fatalities = 50 |survivors = 0 }}
'''Somali Airlines Flight 40''' was a scheduled domestic [[Somali Airlines]] flight on 20 July 1981 from [[Mogadishu]] to [[Hargeisa]] in Somalia. The aircraft crashed a few minutes after takeoff, and all 44 passengers and six crew on board were killed.
==Flight== On 20 July 1981, Somali Airlines Flight 40, operated by a [[Fokker F27 Friendship]], took off from Mogadishu's [[Mogadishu International Airport]] en route to [[Hargeisa International Airport]] in Hargeisa. It later returned to the Mogadishu airport for some repairs, before departing a second time.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=wbxbAAAAIBAJ&sjid=mVINAAAAIBAJ&pg=4460,4139492&dq=somali+airlines+crash&hl=en|title=49 are killed in Somali crash|newspaper=[[St. Joseph News-Press]]|date=20 July 1981|page=3A}}</ref> A few minutes after Flight 40 took off again, the aircraft entered an area of heavy rainfall. The flight crew subsequently lost control and crashed near the town of [[Balad, Somalia|Balad]]. All 50 people on board were killed,<ref>[http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19810720-0 Aircraft accident Fokker F-27 Friendship 600RF 6O-SAY Balad Plane crash claims 49 in Somalia]</ref> the most fatalities in a single aircraft crash within Somali airspace.<ref>[http://aviation-safety.net/database/dblist.php?Country=6O ASN Aviation Safety Database Somalia]</ref>
==Investigation== The crash investigation determined that the aircraft had entered a spiral dive after encountering strong vertical gusts. Loads during the dive increased to approximately 5.76 [[g-force|g]], exceeding the design stress limits of the [[Fokker F27]] type and causing its right wing to separate.<ref>[http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19810720-0 Aircraft accident Fokker F-27 Friendship 600RF 6O-SAY Balad]</ref> The flight crew were believed to have erred in taking off during known thunderstorm conditions.<ref>[http://www.airdisaster.com/cgi-bin/view_details.cgi?date=07201981&reg=6O-SAY&airline=Somali+Airlines Somali Airlines Flight 40 at Airdisaster.com]</ref>
